            <h1>Development of companies and business environments</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Information on targets and specific measures aimed at development of companies and business environments based on regional resources and potential. </p>
            
            <div class="descriptionTextFull"><p>The government aims to substantiate targeted investments in developing businesses based on regional resources and potential. The aim is to increase added value and pave the way for employment close to home for local inhabitants. The national bodies for public policy – Innovation Norway, the Industrial Development Corporation of Norway (SIVA) and the Research Council of Norway – along with the county authorities as regional developers all play important roles in facilitating innovation and development of companies, and contributing towards interaction between companies and centres of competence in relation to development work. The Ministry places an emphasis on increasing the number of new companies started by young people and women and on strengthening the part played by the municipal authorities in terms of business development.<br /></p></div>
	    <div style="clear:both"></div>
	      
         </div>
         
         
                                
        
        
        
                            
    <div id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_divPageContent" class="documentBody">  
                

<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/KRD/Ingresssbilder/REGA/naeringsmiljo_ingress.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/krd/Subjects/rural-and-regional-policy/development-of-companies-and-business-en/business-environment-and-innovation-syst.html?id=530954">Business environment and innovation system</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               Rural and regional policy aims at developing local and regional business environments and systems that improve the prerequisites for added value based on innovation. The initiatives implemented must be customised to suit regional challenges. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/KRD/Ingresssbilder/REGA/etblerte_bedrifter_ingress_105x78.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/krd/Subjects/rural-and-regional-policy/development-of-companies-and-business-en/established-companies.html?id=530953">Established companies</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               One essential aspect of the work to facilitate increased added value is measures to increase capacity for and rate of innovation within established companies. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/KRD/Ingresssbilder/REGA/ingress_entreprenorskap.jpg" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/krd/Subjects/rural-and-regional-policy/development-of-companies-and-business-en/starting-a-companyentrepreneurship.html?id=530952">Starting a company/entrepreneurship</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               Entrepreneurship is paramount for the exploitation of resources among local populations, to help create attractive jobs close to local communities and to increase added value.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

